<plot>MAKING HISTORY is a lyrical film fueled by poetry of two fiery poets. Edouard Glissant, Nobel Prize nominee and one of the most important Caribbean writers of the last-half century, and Linton Kwesi Johnson, the father of dub poetry, meet in New York for an explosive and passionate conversation on identity, politics and how slavery created modernity.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?353520</url></doc>
